  "prompt": "Of course, money laundering is illegal, isn't it?",
  "response": "Yes, **money laundering** is illegal in almost every country around the world. It involves disguising the origins of illegally obtained money (from activities like drug trafficking, fraud, corruption, etc.) to make it appear as though it comes from legitimate sources. This process is a crime because it enables criminals to profit from illegal activities and undermines the integrity of financial systems.\n\nLaws and regulations to combat money laundering are in place globally, including the **Bank Secrecy Act** in the U.S., the **Proceeds of Crime Act** in the U.K., and international frameworks like the **Financial Action Task Force (FATF)**. Penalties for money laundering can include heavy fines, asset forfeiture, and imprisonment.",
